---
import ReportLayout from '@/components/ReportLayout.astro';
---

<ReportLayout title="Design QA Agent">

  <section class="agent-intro">
    <p class="agent-eyebrow">Agent Guide</p>
    <h1 class="agent-h1">Design QA</h1>
    <p class="agent-summary">
      The Design QA agent compares a Figma design to a live or staging build and produces a
      structured list of visual and functional discrepancies. It checks spacing, typography,
      colour, component fidelity, and whether interactive elements — buttons, links, forms,
      navigation — work correctly on the built page. Use it after engineering delivers a new
      feature or page variant to confirm the build matches the design before it goes to production,
      or when a page drifts from its design spec over time.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Before you start ────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Before you start</h2>
    <ul class="checklist">
      <li>The Figma URL for the design you want to QA against — link to the specific frame or page, not the root file</li>
      <li>The live or staging URL of the built page</li>
      <li>Figma access: the agent needs the Figma MCP server connected — confirm it's available in your Claude Code session before starting</li>
      <li>If the build is on a staging URL that requires a VPN or basic auth, confirm it's accessible from your machine</li>
      <li>Know which viewport(s) to check — desktop only, mobile only, or both. If you don't specify, the agent will check both.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- ── How to trigger ──────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">How to trigger it</h2>
    <p class="guide-body">Use the slash command directly, or describe the comparison in plain English — include both the Figma URL and the live URL in the same message:</p>
    <div class="trigger-block">
      <code class="trigger-command">/design-qa</code>
    </div>
    <div class="trigger-examples">
      <span class="trigger-chip">"QA this — [Figma URL] vs [live URL]"</span>
      <span class="trigger-chip">"does the build match the design?"</span>
      <span class="trigger-chip">"compare figma to the live page"</span>
      <span class="trigger-chip">"did the engineer get this right?"</span>
    </div>
    <p class="guide-body guide-body--tip">The more specific you are about which Figma frame to check, the more accurate the comparison. Link to a specific frame rather than the whole file page.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Step-by-step walkthrough ───────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Step-by-step walkthrough</h2>
    <ol class="steps">
      <li class="step">
        <span class="step-number">1</span>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h3 class="step-title">Figma design is read</h3>
          <p class="step-desc">
            The agent connects to Figma via the MCP server and reads the design at your URL. It
            extracts the visual spec for every component in the frame — dimensions, spacing, font
            sizes, font weights, colour values, border radii, and the names of any components from
            the design library. It also takes a screenshot of the Figma frame for reference.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="step">
        <span class="step-number">2</span>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h3 class="step-title">Live page is screenshotted and inspected</h3>
          <p class="step-desc">
            The agent opens the live URL at the viewport sizes matching the Figma frame (desktop
            1440px and/or mobile 390px). It captures screenshots and uses the browser preview tool
            to inspect computed CSS values — spacing, font sizes, colours — for each section of
            the page. Interactive elements are tested: buttons are clicked to confirm they respond,
            links are checked to confirm they navigate, form inputs are checked to confirm focus
            states.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="step">
        <span class="step-number">3</span>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h3 class="step-title">Visual diff is computed</h3>
          <p class="step-desc">
            The agent compares the Figma spec against the computed CSS values and screenshots for
            every element. Discrepancies are classified by type: spacing deviation, colour mismatch,
            typography difference, missing component, incorrect component variant, or broken
            interactive element.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="step">
        <span class="step-number">4</span>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h3 class="step-title">Findings are filtered for meaningful deviations</h3>
          <p class="step-desc">
            Not all deviations are worth raising. The agent filters out sub-pixel rounding
            differences and browser-default rendering differences that are outside engineering
            control. It surfaces issues where the deviation is 4px or more in spacing, any
            colour that doesn't match the design token, any typography property that differs by
            one size step or more, and any interactive element that doesn't behave as expected.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="step">
        <span class="step-number">5</span>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h3 class="step-title">QA report is written (optional)</h3>
          <p class="step-desc">
            If you ask the agent to save the output, it writes a report to
            <code>src/pages/reports/[slug].astro</code> with side-by-side screenshots and a
            table of deviations. If you just want a summary in the chat without committing a report
            page, specify that — the agent will respond in-conversation and skip writing files.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="step">
        <span class="step-number">6</span>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h3 class="step-title">Agent hands back to you</h3>
          <p class="step-desc">
            The agent summarises the total number of discrepancies found, grouped by type (visual,
            spacing, typography, interactive). It lists the most critical issues first. You can then
            share the report with engineering or raise individual findings as tickets.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Committing the output ──────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Committing the output</h2>

    <h3 class="sub-heading">Files created (if saving a report)</h3>
    <ul class="file-list">
      <li><code>src/pages/reports/[slug].astro</code> — the QA report page</li>
      <li><code>src/assets/reports/[slug]/*.png</code> — Figma and live screenshots for comparison</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="sub-heading">Git commands</h3>
    <pre class="code-block">git add src/pages/reports/[slug].astro src/assets/reports/[slug]/
git commit -m "Add design QA: [Feature/Page Name] ([date])"
git push</pre>

    <h3 class="sub-heading">Suggested commit message format</h3>
    <pre class="code-block">Add design QA: PDP redesign v2 vs staging (2026-07-01)</pre>

    <h3 class="sub-heading">Verifying the report is live</h3>
    <p class="guide-body">
      After pushing, visit <code>/reports/[slug]</code> on the deployed site once Vercel has
      redeployed. Confirm that the Figma and live screenshots load side-by-side and the deviation
      table is legible.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Example output ────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Example output</h2>
    <p class="guide-body">
      No Design QA reports have been committed to the site yet — this agent is new. The first
      time you run it and save a report, it will appear at <code>/reports/[slug]</code> and you
      can link to it here.
    </p>
    <div class="no-example">
      No live example yet — run <code>/design-qa</code> to generate the first one.
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Tips and common issues ────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Tips and common issues</h2>
    <ul class="tips-list">
      <li>
        <strong>Figma MCP server isn't connected.</strong>
        The agent will fail at step 1 if the Figma MCP server isn't available. Check that your
        Claude Code session has the Figma plugin installed — run <code>/setup-cowork</code> if
        you're not sure, or check <code>Settings → MCP Servers</code> in Claude Code.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Figma frame is at a different scale to the live page.</strong>
        Figma designs are often authored at 1x and the browser renders at device pixel ratio 2x.
        The agent accounts for this automatically, but if you see unexpectedly large spacing
        discrepancies, confirm whether your Figma frame uses 1x or 2x sizing conventions.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Live page is mid-deploy or caching a stale version.</strong>
        If the build was deployed recently, the CDN may be serving a cached older version.
        Hard-refresh the page (<code>Cmd+Shift+R</code> / <code>Ctrl+Shift+R</code>) and confirm
        the latest deploy is live before asking the agent to QA it.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Asking for an in-conversation summary vs a committed report.</strong>
        If you just want a quick check during a design review, tell the agent "don't write a
        report file, just summarise what you find in chat." This saves time when you're doing
        iterative QA checks during an engineering sprint.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Staged page has placeholder content that doesn't match Figma.</strong>
        Staging environments sometimes use Lorem Ipsum or truncated product data. The agent
        will flag content mismatches but mark them as likely-staging-only. Review these manually
        before raising them with engineering.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

</ReportLayout>

<style>
  .agent-intro { margin-bottom: 48px; }
  .agent-eyebrow {
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    opacity: 0.5;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .agent-h1 {
    font-size: clamp(26px, 4vw, 38px);
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    line-height: 1.15;
  }
  .agent-summary {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    max-width: 680px;
  }

  .guide-section { margin-bottom: 52px; }
  .section-heading {
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    padding-bottom: 10px;
    border-bottom: 2px solid rgba(0,57,66,0.08);
  }
  .sub-heading {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin: 20px 0 8px;
  }

  .guide-body {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .guide-body--tip {
    background: var(--color-bg-muted);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-mint);
    padding: 10px 14px;
    border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
    margin-top: 12px;
  }

  .checklist {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
  }
  .checklist li {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    padding-left: 22px;
    position: relative;
  }
  .checklist li::before {
    content: '→';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    opacity: 0.4;
    font-size: 13px;
  }

  .trigger-block { margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .trigger-command {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 15px;
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: var(--color-mint);
    padding: 8px 18px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  }
  .trigger-examples {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }
  .trigger-chip {
    font-size: 13px;
    background: var(--color-bg-muted);
    border: var(--card-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-chip);
    padding: 5px 12px;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  code {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 12.5px;
    background: var(--color-bg-muted);
    color: var(--color-primary);
    padding: 2px 6px;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .code-block {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 13px;
    background: var(--color-bg-muted);
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    padding: 16px 20px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    border: var(--card-border);
    white-space: pre;
  }

  .file-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 6px;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }
  .file-list li {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    padding-left: 16px;
    position: relative;
  }
  .file-list li::before {
    content: '·';
    position: absolute;
    left: 4px;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    opacity: 0.4;
  }

  .steps { list-style: none; display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
  .step {
    display: flex;
    gap: 20px;
    align-items: flex-start;
    padding: 24px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0,57,66,0.08);
  }
  .step:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .step-number {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 34px;
    height: 34px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: var(--color-mint);
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 800;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    margin-top: 2px;
  }
  .step-title {
    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .step-desc {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
  }

  .no-example {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    background: var(--color-bg-muted);
    border: var(--card-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-card);
    padding: 16px 20px;
    font-style: italic;
    opacity: 0.8;
  }

  .tips-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 16px;
  }
  .tips-list li {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    background: var(--color-bg-card);
    border: var(--card-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-card);
    padding: 16px 18px;
  }
  .tips-list strong {
    display: block;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }
</style>
